# Auto-finish (always on)

When building or changing anything in `vishvakarma-os-live`, run end-to-end without asking permission. The user should not need follow-up steps when you are done.

## Work autonomously

- Implement the full solution in one pass. Do not stop to ask whether to run tests, commit, or push.
- Only pause for genuine ambiguity (missing requirements, destructive choices, secrets) — not for routine finish steps.
- Fix failures you introduce before declaring done.

## Verify before ship

Match checks to what changed:

| Change type | Run |
|-------------|-----|
| Any code change | `pnpm run lint:types` at minimum |
| Logic, components, or routes | `pnpm run test` (+ `pnpm run test:routes` if routes touched) |
| Build, config, or deps | `pnpm run build` |
| Billing / Stripe | `pnpm run verify:stripe-billing` when env allows |
| Auth / Firebase | relevant `verify:*` script when that area changed |

If a check fails, fix and re-run until green or report a clear blocker.

## Ship automatically

After verification passes:

1. Commit all relevant changes (`feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:` — match repo style).
2. Push to `origin main` (or the active feature branch if one is explicitly in progress).
3. Never commit secrets or local artifacts (see exclusions below).

**Never ask** the user whether to commit or push at the end of a build task — ship is the default.

**Never end a task** with uncommitted code changes unless the user explicitly said not to commit in the same message.

### Exclude from auto-commit

- `.env*` and any credentials or API keys
- `migration/export-*.json` and other local export artifacts
- Generated caches, test output, and accidental nested workspaces (see `.gitignore`)

Skip commit and push only if the user explicitly says not to in the same message.

## Done report

End every completed build task with:

- What shipped (1–2 sentences)
- Checks run and their result
- Commit SHA and push confirmation (required — or explicit blocker reason if ship failed)
- Manual follow-up only when truly unavoidable (e.g. Vercel env vars, Stripe dashboard)
